Package: scDiffCom
Type: Package
Title: Differential analysis of Intercellular Communication from scRNA-seq data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Cyril", "Lagger", email = "lagger.cyril@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Eugen", "Ursu", email = "ursu_eugen@hotmail.com",
    role = c("aut")),
    person("Anais", "Equey", email = "anais.equey@gmail.com",
    role = c("ctb"))
    )
Description: A statistical method to perform differential analyis of
    intercellular communication from single-cell transcriptomics data.
    From a pre-processed Seurat object as input, it infers cell-cell
    interactions present in the dataset and how these interactions changes
    between two conditions of interest (e.g. young vs old). It relies on an 
    internal database of ligand-receptor interactions that has been gathered
    from several published studies. The statistical method relies on a 
    permutation test. The package also implements several tools to perform
    downstream analysis and visualize the results.
